It's great that you're feeling sharper on the job and that your pants are fitting better.  Everyone's body is different, and it can take some trial and error to find a routine that works for you.

Just be sure to listen to your body. If you're feeling sluggish, dizzy, or experience other negative symptoms, you might need to make some adjustments. It's also a good idea to make sure you're getting all the nutrients your body needs.

A brief period of fasting or calorie restriction can be safe for many adults, with modest weight loss and improvements in certain markers of health.&#x20;

If you're comfortable with how things are going, that's great. Stick to your routine and celebrate each big and small victory along the way.&#x20;

If you ever find that you're not feeling well or that your routine isn't working for you anymore, there are lots of resources available to you. Consider reaching out to a healthcare professional, such as a doctor or a registered dietitian, for advice on maintaining a healthy diet. They can help you make a personalized plan that is tailored to your lifestyle and nutritional needs.&#x20;

Eat normally, without stressing about this or that. Aim for a balanced diet with plenty of fruits, vegetables, lean proteins, and whole grains. If you're feeling overwhelmed or unsure, there's always support available.
